abstract: New entrants into the race. A nod from Barack Obama. Centrist victories in governor’s contests. Moderates sense a favorable shift.
snippet: New entrants into the race. A nod from Barack Obama. Centrist victories in governor’s contests. Moderates sense a favorable shift.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — After spending months in anxious passivity, staking their hopes on Joseph R. Biden Jr. and little else, moderate Democrats appear suddenly determined to fight for control of their party in the 2020 elections.

abstract: His apology for the stop-and-frisk policy is politically convenient.
snippet: His apology for the stop-and-frisk policy is politically convenient.
lead_paragraph: Last Sunday I wrote a column entitled “You Must Never Vote for Bloomberg” because of Michael Bloomberg’s promotion, advocacy and defense of the racist stop-and-frisk policy that ballooned during his terms as mayor of New York City.

abstract: With Gordon Sondland prepared to testify this week, Republicans backed away from complaints about secondhand information and instead offered a blunter defense: The president did nothing wrong.
snippet: With Gordon Sondland prepared to testify this week, Republicans backed away from complaints about secondhand information and instead offered a blunter defense: The president did nothing wrong.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Republicans, bracing for another week of impeachment hearings, asserted on Sunday that President Trump had done nothing wrong because his plans for Ukraine to investigate his political rivals never came to fruition — even as the president complicated their efforts by attacking another witness.

abstract: Ahead of a possible Democratic run for president, the former mayor of New York City reversed himself before an important party constituency: black voters.
snippet: Ahead of a possible Democratic run for president, the former mayor of New York City reversed himself before an important party constituency: black voters.
lead_paragraph: Ahead of a potential Democratic presidential run, former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York on Sunday reversed his longstanding support of the aggressive “stop-and-frisk” policing strategy that he pursued for a decade and that led to the disproportionate stopping of black and Latino people across the city.

abstract: Mr. Buttigieg had a surprisingly robust lead in the latest Des Moines Register and CNN poll. Elizabeth Warren, Bernie Sanders and Joseph R. Biden Jr. were in a statistical tie for second.
snippet: Mr. Buttigieg had a surprisingly robust lead in the latest Des Moines Register and CNN poll. Elizabeth Warren, Bernie Sanders and Joseph R. Biden Jr. were in a statistical tie for second.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Pete Buttigieg continues to surge in Iowa, leapfrogging Senator Elizabeth Warren and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to hold a commanding lead among likely Democratic caucusgoers, according to a new poll from The Des Moines Register and CNN.

abstract: Some civil servants will endure only so much abuse and scandal before speaking up.
snippet: Some civil servants will endure only so much abuse and scandal before speaking up.
lead_paragraph: The opening hearings on the Ukraine scandal demonstrated that mundane government processes and seemingly colorless bureaucrats are what keep our country going. It was these sorts of unknown public servants who maintained the executive branch functioning during Watergate — and are doing so now while our distracted president and his acolytes try to circumvent the rules.

abstract: 2 days of public hearings. How did we get here? Allegations of bribery. And more.
snippet: 2 days of public hearings. How did we get here? Allegations of bribery. And more.
lead_paragraph: Marie L. Yovanovitch, the former ambassador to Ukraine and longtime diplomat, testified on Friday, the second day of public hearings in the impeachment inquiry, about her time in Ukraine. She spoke from decades of diplomatic experience about the situation there and about her removal and the way she was treated by President Trump.

abstract: Here are five things happened on the presidential campaign trail this week, as impeachment hearings began in Washington.
snippet: Here are five things happened on the presidential campaign trail this week, as impeachment hearings began in Washington.
lead_paragraph: There was more upheaval in the 2020 race this week, as one new Democratic candidate entered, another moved closer to doing so and a Republican dropped his primary challenge to President Trump. Here’s a look at the highlights.

abstract: Now there’s witness intimidation and clearer evidence he had no interest in cleaning up Ukraine.
snippet: Now there’s witness intimidation and clearer evidence he had no interest in cleaning up Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: Republican defenders of Donald Trump have argued that he withheld congressionally mandated military aid to Ukraine and a promised White House meeting because he wanted assurances that Ukraine’s new president, Volodymyr Zelensky, was serious about fighting corruption.
